#: ../../source/mdt.rst:2
msgid "MDT – The OpenModelica Development Tooling Eclipse Plugin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:10
msgid ""
"The Modelica Development Tooling (MDT) Eclipse Plugin as part of OMDev – "
"The OpenModelica Development Environment integrates the OpenModelica "
"compiler with Eclipse. MDT, together with the OpenModelica compiler, "
"provides an environment for working with Modelica and MetaModelica "
"development projects. This plugin is primarily intended for tool "
"developers rather than application Modelica modelers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:17
msgid "The following features are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:19
msgid "Browsing support for Modelica projects, packages, and classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:21
msgid "Wizards for creating Modelica projects, packages, and classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:23
msgid "Syntax color highlighting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:25
msgid "Syntax checking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:27
msgid "Browsing of the Modelica Standard Library or other libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:29
msgid "Code completion for class names and function argument lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:31
msgid "Goto definition for classes, types, and functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:33
msgid "Displaying type information when hovering the mouse over an identifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:37
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:39
msgid ""
"The installation of MDT is accomplished by following the below "
"installation instructions. These instructions assume that you have "
"successfully downloaded and installed Eclipse (http://www.eclipse.org)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:43
msgid ""
"The latest installation instructions are available through the "
"`OpenModelica Trac <https://trac.openmodelica.org/MDT>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:45
msgid "Start Eclipse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:47
msgid "Select Help->Software Updates->Find and Install.\\ **..** from the menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:50
msgid "Select ‘Search for new features to install’ and click ‘Next’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:52
msgid "Select ‘New Remote Site...’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:54
msgid ""
"Enter ‘MDT’ as name and "
"http://www.ida.liu.se/labs/pelab/modelica/OpenModelica/MDT as URL and "
"click ‘OK’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:58
msgid "Make sure ‘MDT’ is selected and click ‘Finish’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:60
msgid "In the updates dialog select the ‘MDT’ feature and click ‘Next’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:62
msgid "Read through the license agreement, select ‘I accept...’ and click ‘Next’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:65
msgid "Click ‘Finish’ to install MDT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:68
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:71
msgid "Configuring the OpenModelica Compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:73
msgid ""
"MDT needs to be able to locate the binary of the compiler. It uses the "
"environment variable OPENMODELICAHOME to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:76
msgid ""
"If you have problems using MDT, make sure that OPENMODELICAHOME is "
"pointing to the folder where the OpenModelica Compiler is installed. In "
"other words, OPENMODELICAHOME must point to the folder that contains the "
"Open Modelica Compiler (OMC) binary. On the Windows platform it’s called "
"omc.exe and on Unix platforms it’s called omc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:83
msgid "Using the Modelica Perspective"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:85
msgid ""
"The most convenient way to work with Modelica projects is to use to the "
"Modelica perspective. To switch to the Modelica perspective, choose the "
"Window menu item, pick Open Perspective followed by Other\\ **...** "
"Select the Modelica option from the dialog presented and click OK.."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:91
msgid "Selecting a Workspace Folder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:93
msgid ""
"Eclipse stores your projects in a folder called a workspace. You need to "
"choose a workspace folder for this session, see :numref:`mdt-switch-"
"workspace`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:99
msgid "Eclipse Setup – Switching Workspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:102
msgid "Creating one or more Modelica Projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:104
msgid ""
"To start a new project, use the New Modelica Project Wizard. It is "
"accessible through File->New-> Modelica Project or by right-clicking in "
"the Modelica Projects view and selecting New->Modelica Project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:110
msgid "Eclipse Setup – creating a Modelica project in the workspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:112
msgid ""
"You need to disable automatic build for the project(s) (:numref:`mdt-"
"disable-automatic-build`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:117
msgid "Eclipse Setup – disable automatic build for the projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:119
msgid ""
"Repeat the procedure for all the projects you need, e.g. for the "
"exercises described in the MetaModelica users guide: 01\\_experiment, "
"02a\\_exp1, 02b\\_exp2, 03\\_assignment, 04a\\_assigntwotype, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:123
msgid ""
"NOTE: Leave open only the projects you are working on! Close all the "
"others!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:127
msgid "Building and Running a Project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:129
msgid ""
"After having created a project, you eventually need to build the project "
"(:numref:`mdt-build-project`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:135
msgid "Eclipse MDT – Building a project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:137
msgid ""
"The build options are the same as the make targets: you can build, build "
"from scratch (clean), or run simulations depending on how the project is "
"setup. See :numref:`mdt-build-prompt` for an example of how omc can be "
"compiled (:bash:`make omc` builds OMC)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:145
msgid "Eclipse – building a project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:149
msgid "Eclipse – building a project, resulting log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:152
msgid "Switching to Another Perspective"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:154
msgid ""
"If you need, you can (temporarily) switch to another perspective, e.g. to"
" the Java perspective for working with an OpenModelica Java client as in "
":numref:`mdt-switch-perspective`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:161
msgid "Eclipse – Switching to another perspective – e.g. the Java Perspective."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:164
msgid "Creating a Package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:166
msgid ""
"To create a new package inside a Modelica project, select "
"File->New->Modelica Package\\ **.** Enter the desired name of the package"
" and a description of what it contains. Note: for the exercises we "
"already have existing packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:173
msgid "Creating a new Modelica package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:176
msgid "Creating a Class"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:178
msgid ""
"To create a new Modelica class, select where in the hierarchy that you "
"want to add your new class and select File->New->Modelica Class. When "
"creating a Modelica class you can add different restrictions on what the "
"class can contain. These can for example be model, connector, block, "
"record, or function. When you have selected your desired class type, you "
"can select modifiers that add code blocks to the generated code. ‘Include"
" initial code block’ will for example add the line ‘initial equation’ to "
"the class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:189
msgid "Creating a new Modelica class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:192
msgid "Syntax Checking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:194
msgid ""
"Whenever a build command is given to the MDT environment, modified and "
"saved Modelica (.mo) files are checked for syntactical errors. Any errors"
" that are found are added to the Problems view and also marked in the "
"source code editor. Errors are marked in the editor as a red circle with "
"a white cross, a squiggly red line under the problematic construct, and "
"as a red marker in the right-hand side of the editor. If you want to "
"reach the problem, you can either click the item in the Problems view or "
"select the red box in the right-hand side of the editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:205
msgid "Syntax checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:208
msgid "Automatic Indentation Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:210
msgid ""
"MDT currently has support for automatic indentation. When typing the "
"Return (Enter) key, the next line is indented correctly. You can also "
"correct indentation of the current line or a range selection using CTRL+I"
" or “Correct Indentation” action on the toolbar or in the Edit menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:217
msgid "Code Completion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:219
msgid ""
"MDT supports Code Completion in two variants. The first variant, code "
"completion when typing a dot after a class (package) name, shows "
"alternatives in a menu. Besides the alternatives, Modelica documentation "
"from comments is shown if is available. This makes the selection easyer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:226
msgid "Code completion when typing a dot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:228
msgid ""
"The second variant is useful when typing a call to a function. It shows "
"the function signature (formal parameter names and types) in a popup when"
" typing the parenthesis after the function name, here the signature Real "
"sin(SI.Angle u) of the sin function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:235
msgid "Code completion at a function call when typing left parenthesis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:238
msgid "Code Assistance on Identifiers when Hovering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:240
msgid ""
"When hovering with the mouse over an identifier a popup with information "
"about the identifier is displayed. If the text is too long, the user can "
"press F2 to focus the popup dialog and scroll up and down to examine all "
"the text. As one can see the information in the popup dialog is syntax-"
"highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:248
msgid "Displaying information for identifiers on hovering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:251
msgid "Go to Definition Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:253
msgid ""
"Besides hovering information the user can press CTRL+click to go to the "
"definition of the identifier. When pressing CTRL the identifier will be "
"presented as a link and when pressing mouse click the editor will go to "
"the definition of the identifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:259
msgid "Code Assistance on Writing Records"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:261
msgid ""
"When writing records, the same functionality as for function calls is "
"used. This is useful especially in MetaModelica when writing cases in "
"match constructs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/mdt.rst:267
msgid "Code assistance when writing cases with records in MetaModelica."
msgstr ""

